This paper is primarily focused on robotic manipulation skills, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of learning algorithms to improve manipulation skills, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of sensors and perception in the learning process may also relate to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of constraints to improve manipulation skills, which may relate to control systems (cs.SY).
